    "id": 3,
    "date": "Jan 2026",
    "title": "Vibe-coded a demo that felt already shipped",
    "body": "We needed to validate a complex workflow before a single line of production code was written. Figma Make let us build something that felt real enough to actually test.",
    "tags": [
      "Figma",
      "Design"
    ],
    "logos": [
      "/figma-make.svg"
    ],
    "thumbBg": "#F0F0FF",
    "image": null,
    "heroImage": "/uploads/figma-make-hero.png",
    "fullContent": "<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">I was designing a workflow builder. Ten types of nodes. AI triggers, sequences, actions, testing, history. Every node had its own behavior.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><b>Prototyping something this complex is nearly impossible. Too many states, too many paths. </b>A Figma prototype would take weeks just to wire up the happy path.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">I tried Cursor first. The problem wasn't the code — it was the design system. Making it look exactly like our product would take just as long as building the real thing. And I only needed the front end. I didn't need any of the backend.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">So I tried Figma Make. 95% of it matched my Figma exactly. <b>In about a few hours, I had a fully interactive prototype that looked like the real product.</b></p><div class=\"demo-card\" data-demo-url=\"https://plays.nooks.in/\"></div>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">Two things happened from there.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><b>First, engineers could finally see the interactions clearly.</b> Less back-and-forth. Less \"what happens when you click this?\" The prototype answered those questions before they were asked.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"><b>Second, we used this as a demo for potential customers two months before it was built. </b>We used it to demo to customers and collect feedback before a single line of production code was written.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\">Later, when we launched our new website, I refined it. The prototype became an interactive demo embedded on our website and inside the product itself. It looked real enough that customers could actually evaluate it.</p>\n<p class=\"font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]\"></p>",
